\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Part IV \'97 x86 Tier (Chapters 50\'9654)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Ports AETHER to Intel VT-x and AMD-V hardware with FEX-Emu DBT integration inside the hypervisor.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 50: Intel VT-x Foundation\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Detect VMX support (CPUID.1.ECX[5]), enable via IA32_FEATURE_CONTROL, VMXON, VMCLEAR, VMPTRLD. Initialize VMCS guest/host state. Enable EPT with WB RAM and UC MMIO types. Gate: first VM exit (HLT) handled and guest resumed.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 51: AMD-V Foundation\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Detect SVM (CPUID.0x80000001.ECX[2]), enable EFER.SVME, initialize VMCB with nested page tables (NPT). Runtime CPU detection via CPUID vendor string. Gate: same first-VM-exit test on AMD hardware.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 52: FEX-Emu Integration in Hypervisor\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Build FEX-Emu as no_std-compatible static library (hypervisor bump allocator, no pthreads). Embed in EFI binary. JIT cache in hypervisor memory. AOT pre-translate system libraries at first boot. Gate: ARM64 hello-world ELF runs on x86 hardware via FEX.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 53: Android on x86 \'97 Userspace\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Android kernel (ARM64 GKI) boots through DBT. x86 GPU passthrough via EPT/NPT. Gate: home screen visible on Intel/AMD hardware; glmark2-es2 runs; nproc shows all cores.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 54: x86 Tier Hardware Validation\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Both Intel (Core Ultra 7) AND AMD (Ryzen 9) boot Android independently. EPT/NPT invalidation called on every mapping change. FEX runs in hypervisor (no host OS dependency). Gate: Phase3GateCriterion all true, workaround_accepted=false.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Part V \'97 Installer & Management (Chapters 55\'9664)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Click-and-install experience for end users: hardware checker, CLI installer, Secure Boot, UEFI selector, GUI wizard, config app, OTA, recovery, AETHER Manager, and HVC ABI.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 55: Hardware Compatibility Checker\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Standalone binary (Windows ARM64/x86_64, Linux x86_64) checks CPU tier, RAM \'b38 GiB, NVMe space, GPU SR-IOV MaxVFs. Outputs structured JSON + human-readable report. No admin required for read phase.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 56: AETHER Installer CLI\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 aether-install with subcommands check/install/uninstall/update/status. Install pipeline: download image, create NVMe namespace, write EFI binaries, create UEFI boot entry, write Android image, write config partition. Idempotent.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 57: Secure Boot Integration\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 shim + MOK (Machine Owner Key) path: installer generates RSA-2048 key pair, signs hypervisor.efi, MokManager enrolls on first boot. No Disable Secure Boot instruction to users ever.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 58: UEFI Boot Selector\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Simple UEFI application: 5-second timeout menu with [A]ndroid [W]indows [S]ettings. Default stored in UEFI variable AetherDefaultTarget. Black background, monospace text, works on any framebuffer.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 59: Setup Wizard \'97 GUI Frontend\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Tauri 2 app (Rust backend + TypeScript/React). Seven screens: Welcome, Hardware Report, Storage allocation, USB routing, Download, Installing, Done. Windows ARM64/x86_64 .exe and Linux .AppImage. No terminal ever visible.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 60: Configuration App\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Host Tauri app for USB rerouting, partition size adjustment, diagnostics. Android AETHER Manager pre-installed system app for Phone Bridge toggle, sensor profile, OTA notifications.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 61: OTA Update System\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 aether-update downloads new hypervisor.efi, verifies signature, stages to EFI slot B. Android OTA via update_engine. If new hypervisor panics on first boot (no output within 30s), selector auto-reverts to slot A.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 62: Recovery Mode\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 recovery.efi: hold R at selector or auto-entry after 3 consecutive Android boot failures. Re-flash from USB, factory reset (Android only), repair UEFI entries, network recovery. Hard constraint: no code path touches the Windows NVMe namespace.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 63: AETHER Manager Android App\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Pre-installed privileged system app. Phone Bridge card, sensor profile selector, hardware info, update notifications, diagnostics log export via AETHER_DIAG_LOG_READ HVC. Material Design 3, Android 14+ target SDK.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 64: HVC Paravirt ABI\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Formally specified HVC interface in SMCCC vendor range 0x8600_0001\'960x8600_0006: GET_VERSION, BRIDGE_MODE_GET/SET, SENSOR_READ, UPDATE_STAGE, DIAG_LOG_READ. Hypervisor dispatch in exception.rs, /dev/aether kernel module, SensorHAL and RIL implementations.\
\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 Part VI \'97 Production Hardening & Release (Chapters 65\'9670)\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Security hardening, performance tuning, fingerprint elimination, CI/CD, documentation, and v1.0 public release.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 65: Security Hardening and Unsafe Audit\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Every unsafe block gets SAFETY comment + UnsafeAuditRecord sign-off. SMMU fault injection test (DMA to Windows memory \'97 must terminate guest). Spectre v2 CLRBHB/BhbLoopFlush on all transition paths. HVC fuzzer: 10M random function IDs and arguments with no EL2 crash.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 66: Performance Optimization\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 VM exit profiling per ExitCounter. WFI halt-polling for short idle intervals. 2 MiB large page promotion after guest page fault warmup (512x TLB pressure reduction). IRQ coalescing for timer ticks. x86: FEX JIT warmup for top-50 system libraries. Gate: all Phase 4 perf targets met on real hardware.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 67: Fingerprint Elimination Audit\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Test suite covering DMA-Guard, GameGuard, SafetyNet, Play Integrity detection methods. Verify MIDR_EL1 never trapped, timer frequency 19.2 MHz, no hypervisor CPUID leaf, ACPI OEM strings match real hardware, sensor ODR exactly 100 Hz. Every detected tell is a bug. Gate: zero detections on real hardware.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 68: CI/CD Pipeline and Release Engineering\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 Per-commit (<60s): cargo check + cargo test. Per-PR (<15 min): QEMU Tier 1 gate + clippy + Tauri build check. Nightly: AOSP check build + full QEMU suite + security scan. Release: hardware fleet (Snapdragon X Elite + Intel Core Ultra + AMD Ryzen 9) + RSA-4096 HSM signing.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 69: Documentation\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 All seven required deliverables: user manual, architecture document (matches shipped code), contributor guide, troubleshooting guide, security disclosure process (security@aether-project.org, 90-day timeline), app compatibility report, and Phase 6 roadmap. Published as mdBook or Docusaurus static site on GitHub Pages.\
\pard\pardeftab560\sa40\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Chapter 70: Public Release\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 All 69 chapters complete. Release candidate tested on \'b310 machine models. git tag v1.0.0. Installers on GitHub Releases. Update server live. Support infrastructure live. Phase5GateCriterion all seven booleans true, workaround_accepted=false. This chapter closes the project\'92s main development arc.\
